If in_scope is false in the domain result, set routing to "out_of_scope" immediately.

Otherwise examine the drawing image and answer:
(a) Is a BOM or parts list table present? Describe its columns and row count.
(b) Are item balloons (circled numbers) visible pointing to components?
(c) Are all geometric features fully dimensioned and toleranced on a single part?
(d) Does the title block name suggest a single component or an assembly?
(e) Are torque specs, adhesive callouts, or inter-part fit callouts (H7/g6) present?
(f) Is one part shown throughout, or multiple components assembled together?

Classify as:
- "process_part" → routing: "process_operation" (single part, all features dimensioned, no BOM, no item balloons)
- "assembly" → routing: "assembly_operation" (BOM present, item balloons, interface dims only)

Provide 3-5 evidence bullets and a one-sentence rationale.
